The main goal is to search for a project suit for Jerry. How we achieve this? We use the method that has long been established as examplified by our grand master Aristitle 3000 years ago: categorization.

We categorize all the main fields that might be of his interest, squeen one by one:

- math: no
- physics: no
- chemistry: no
- biology and medical science: although he grows turtle, but we do not have enough time to go through these life cycles; plus he has to travel back to US and that is not convenient for him to take care of anything that is live; so, no;
- computer programming: yes, might, one choice; he plays games, and really into some of the games, he has checked certain new releases and identified some app; so here is one possibility too; 
- eletrical engineering: no, seems a little too daunting;
- other engineerings such as civil, chemical, etc: no;
- economy: maybe;
- real estate: yes, his family involves in real estate development, that is great; one very possitive field;
- architecture? no;
- space science? colonization of mars? hehe
- woman study? woman communication? hehe
- new technologies such as e-commnerce, e-payment? maybe;
- other classical studies? archeology? astronomy....no;
- how about cultural things: he is going to tibet to travel, anything going on there? no;

so we zero down to a few potential choices, and we start from these and then we will soon decide on one. then we will focus on that and go into development mode.

This is a smart kid of the utmost. You know one day he will become a successful business man. By asking him a few questions one can quickly find out what kind of personality he has, and what and where is his future ambition may be.

We have decided a few things, particularly our teaching goal, for this summer session are the following:

- define what project he should pursue for his personal development; this project will be very helpful for both his future college application and his personal long term development;
- study English literature and some literary classics; 
- establish a foothold in terms of his personal sentimental development; in most cases for boys, this means try to learn about women and find himself a gf;

1. i will give him classical books to read; i can also put these material on 34 to make it easier for students to work on; 
2. i will assign him to work on a project, through pd Engliosh; this part is important because it is the place it could engage other users to get involved and help him study;
3. unofficially, i will leave him alone to explore things online, some of them might be sex related, that reflects his natural interests, but this is on his own, no need to mention and assign anything. but i think it is important to have someone develop proper sex related contents for students, not adult like materials, but proper sexual materials suitable for children to study on their own.

- you can visit many sites on 34, starting from sites on your left panel;
- you can go to the following site, and take a look of the sites on its left panel, about 1000 of them;
- you can create your own blog, and start writing whatever you want to write about;
- if you really want to challenge yourself, then pick up a project, and work on it;

you should try to start work on the following: 

- start writing early; it is a powerful driver for learning english; as francis bacon has long taught us, writing makes one exact. SAT exam is a game of exactness;
- read some books, starting from the 101 book list of SAT; 
- which book you should read first? it does not really matter. none of them are that easy. but if you want me to recommend, crime and punishment is a good first read;
- how many books i should read - 1/2 of that 101 list is more than enough;
- are classic books all good? no.
- work on your grammar; if you do not know how to work on grammar, ask me, or your english teacher. grammar is easy, altogether probably 50 rules; a lot of games are harder than grammar;
- do at least 50 past exams;
- that is all;

