harvard is just an institution of a group of people. these group of people will act on zero. how it will be featured by these harverders would be an interesting act. here are a few points - 

- there is never a need for official harvard presence on zero; harvard is and never will be zero; it thinks itself much bigger, and it is indeed bigger;
- but it will inevitably talked about and described by zeros, many of them are zeros going to harvard; so harvard will loom and take on a form through the words of these harvard zeros;
- there is no question this formation will be quite different from what we know and what we are intended to know; sure there would be some dirt flying and secrets unrevealed;
- then there will be a conflict; maybe even a fight, that is what zeros need to prepare for;
- but this will not just be a zero sum game; 
- what we collectively gain will be discussed further later;

what he could do to the best of his advancement?

- he could use his preprietary knowledge to pretend he is a professor;
- he could pretend to be a guru and gain attention of a female student for potential dating;
- he could trade his knowledge for other personal gains;

what he would prefer to do on 0-34 to his best advantage? 

- given his status already he has nothing to gain by letting others know who he is;
- so he could pretend to be a student, asking naive questions to gain insight of what is going on among his students and other faculties;
- he could pretend to be an complete outsider and probe the minds of his competitors and professors of other universities;

so, a critical question is 
- how a professor should be featured on 0-34?
- would unofficial version of him be allowed? there could be many versions of him of course, but if someone choose to feature him and even pretend to be him, what others could do? and should do? probably there will never be a way to tell who is who and witch is the real;

- you interact freely, but never bother to ask who i am; 
- you interact freely, but never try to meet face to face or my book of face;
- you interact freely, but never try ot ask for my email, phone number, and so on....right here, it suggests taht one day indeed phone number will become obsolete for many;
- so this is a pure platonic thing, i think women would prefer to interact this way, at least to start with; so this promises one day more women could use 0-34 than men;

traditonal centralized place has its quality, but can not replaced a self centered platform, a distributed platform. man creates in solitude, where he himself has to home him and be his world. zero and 34 give him such a homeplace, to me that is the best place to be. i call it a farm.

so zero and 34 can be a creativity farm. the question is how to formulate it to best serve this purpose. 

here is some starting thoughts -

- each one has to work through his own blogsite, or something developed out of that, but basically it is a self centered personal farm; on his farm he mostly work by himself;
- these farms are connected in numerous ways;
- ai fercilitate inter-farming communications;
- great ideas and projects will be nurtured by collective resources that are accumulated through certain algorithm;

some people have given valuable suggestions and here i will layout the key points for a zero college implementation, i will update this from time to time:

- it is a decentralized college, not just from the technical perspective, but also from many other senses, for example, from the way it is managed - as for what is the key traits of a decentralized management and admin, i will discuss that in as a special topic;
- it should co-exist in a parallel way vs other traditional institutions; i don't think it will destablize any, but z-college will provide complementary values;
- tuition, well as its name has suggested, zero;
- faculty salaries: zero too; they work on donations and competing for public and private research grants;
- budgeting: extremely low, close to zero; if there is any funding need, would rely mostly on donation;
- it will look to obtain accreditation from all major countries in the future;

its unique advantage comparing to traditional centralized establishement contains: 

- ability to organize and network almost everyone on earth;
- ability to scale up on any topic or project infinitely and quickly;
- its extremely low cost of admin and infrastructure;
- its inherent ease on communication and transaction;
- its effectiveness in providing important services such as employment, dating, and etc
- its collective creativity
- and most of all, it is a game
- its complete flat and demacratic nature, which enables incredible values in its communication power such as news and new media

please feel completely free to add, modify, and comment.

thank you all.

