writing is the hardest part of learning any language. here at 34 we champion a way of learning - learning by writing. 

it is hard, but it is perfectably doable. you pick up your pen, (i mean pen), then do something with it. it shows, it flows, it works. what to write about? here are some starting points -

three word theory of writing:

- write whatever you are thinking about, right now;
- decide on the first word; 
- how to pick the first word? the word that comes to your mind, right now;
- once the first word is set, then follow that by the second word; the second word is influenced and related to your first word;
- think about the relation between these two words, what should be used to link them? that comes the third word;
- with three words on the paper, you are writing now.

